X200T_CHANGES: Adresse 44 er tilføjet. Hvis 44 = 1, så dæmpes display lyset ikke, når der køres ud af rullefelt. Dette er lavet til USA.Adresse 236 er default ændret fra 4 til 6I PKW mode blev der på UK print ikke skrevet reference værdier på. Dette gør der nu. 50% for service og 16/25% for parkering. Der var problemer med adresse 198 og hvis speed sensor var frakoblet. Dette problem er fikset.Adresse 199 er tilføjet. Den bestemmer min. Grænsen for bremseforskel visning for LKW køretøjer (Lastbil). Eks. 199 = 0 (default 400 daN), 199 =  6 (300 daN). Altså step af 50 daN og hvis 199 = 0, så er den default 400.Adresse 258 er tilføjet. Den bestemmer retur trykket for CLS. Den var før hardcoded til 15 bar, nu er den default 40 bar, men kan ændres.En lille fejl i forbindelse med B-Mode og suspension testeren er også rettet.

When infrared [kg] is pressed, the weight will show left/right/both.Then “0” is pressed before “print” in service mode, no printout! GUID from test map has been added to key_data.  Only Sweden Evaluation of axle removed from Swedish printout.If Pm is larger than +/- 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring, the Pm display will show lines “—“. If no P0 measured the Pm display will switch between lines “—“ and the block pressure after the test.When infrared [Ovality] is pressed, the tester will freeze values when average values are measured. (Same as eprom Version 12 ASB).

Nu vises resultatet i 10 sek.

X200T_CHANGES: (Only L1)---The printout for the Danish car inspection has changed. -	The ovality reference has change from ex. 30% -> +/-15%.-	The total test deceleration is removed.Corrections in the P0 calculation “Only DK”Acceleration due to gravity is change from 0.0982 to 0.0981.  ---When going into service mode, the X200 will start sending realtime data to the PC every 50mS. It was very difficult to adjust the weight from the PC screen with sending data only every 200mS.A standard BM Source Code Cleaning is done to get more space :o).

X010T_CHANGES: When config 29 = 1, the pedal force is added to brake force, the analog signal is then scaled 0-255 daN instead of 0-99 daN which is normal. The SR number is added to config 192 and is being sent with the key pack to the PC.Many customers have complained that the update rate of the display pointers was very slow. It is because the communication line is very busy. Many customers do not have an ECPU, so on power up the system will check if the ECPU is connected. If not, the communication to the ECPU will stop. A power cycle needs to be done to restart the communication.The time before middle roller speed check was hardcoded to 500mS. Config 107 is now added and makes it possible to adjust the time (Min 500mS and Max. 1500mS). The reason for this config is, that some testers with soft starters could not startup (Iceland).  If the car was thrown out of the rollers just after start it took 1sec before the motor was stopped. It is now fixed and the motor is stopped immediately.The sideslip value now has a max and a min value. +/-15. Ex. If sideslip measured is -26 it will be set to -15.The RS232 receive function is improved.   Iceland language is added.

X200T_CHANGES: If any address is out of range, that address will be set to default.New address 80 for A/B mode (Single roller bed). 0-Can NOT be activated (default)1-Can be activatedNew address 189 for brake force interval for P0 calculation (Step of 10daN).        1-15 (Default 2)        Ex. 2 =20 daN.New P0 calculationThe P0 calculation could not be done if the Pm had been more that 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring. This is change so, the difference of Pm must NOT be larger than +/- 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring. New rules and calculations for Denmark (Disk (A mode) / Drum (B mode) brake is selected with A/B)-Only special printout will show the Danish result.Address 253: default value change to 6New bit in realtime packet to switch between show ovality / frequency . (This is for you Steffen)-sbit ctrlTenKiloStep = ctrlInfo^0 -sbit ctrlShowFreq = ctrlInfo^1In service mode the weight can now manually be controlled. When infrared [kg] is pressed, the weight will show left/right/both.Then “0” is pressed before “print” in service mode, no printout! GUID from test map has been added to key_data.  Only Sweden Evaluation of axle removed from Swedish printout.If Pm is larger than +/- 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring, the Pm display will show lines “—“. If no P0 measured the Pm display will switch between lines “—“ and the block pressure after the test.When infrared [Ovality] is pressed, the tester will freeze values when average values are measured. (Same as eprom Version 12 ASB).

X010T_CHANGES: When config 29 = 1, the pedal force is added to brake force, the analog signal is then scaled 0-255 daN instead of 0-99 daN which is normal. The SR number is added to config 192 and is being sent with the key pack to the PC.Many customers have complained that the update rate of the display pointers was very slow. It is because the communication line is very busy. Many customers do not have an ECPU, so on power up the system will check if the ECPU is connected. If not, the communication to the ECPU will stop. A power cycle needs to be done to restart the communication.The time before middle roller speed check was hardcoded to 500mS. Config 107 is now added and makes it possible to adjust the time (Min 500mS and Max. 1500mS). The reason for this config is, that some testers with soft starters could not startup (Iceland).  If the car was thrown out of the rollers just after start it took 1sec before the motor was stopped. It is now fixed and the motor is stopped immediately.The sideslip value now has a max and a min value. +/-15. Ex. If sideslip measured is -26 it will be set to -15.The RS232 receive function is improved.   Iceland language is added.
X200T_CHANGES: (Only L1)---The printout for the Danish car inspection has changed. -	The ovality reference has change from ex. 30% -> +/-15%.-	The total test deceleration is removed.Corrections in the P0 calculation “Only DK”Acceleration due to gravity is change from 0.0982 to 0.0981.  ---When going into service mode, the X200 will start sending realtime data to the PC every 50mS. It was very difficult to adjust the weight from the PC screen with sending data only every 200mS.A standard BM Source Code Cleaning is done to get more space :o).

Config 107 is now added and makes it possible to adjust the time (Min 500mS and Max. 1500mS). The reason for this config is, that some testers with soft starters could not startup (Iceland). X200T_CHANGES: If any address is out of range, that address will be set to default.New address 80 for A/B mode (Single roller bed). 0-Can NOT be activated (default)1-Can be activatedNew address 189 for brake force interval for P0 calculation (Step of 10daN).        1-15 (Default 2)        Ex. 2 =20 daN.New P0 calculationThe P0 calculation could not be done if the Pm had been more that 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring. This is change so, the difference of Pm must NOT be larger than +/- 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring. New rules and calculations for Denmark (Disk (A mode) / Drum (B mode) brake is selected with A/B)-Only special printout will show the Danish result.Address 253: default value change to 6New bit in realtime packet to switch between show ovality / frequency . (This is for you Steffen)-sbit ctrlTenKiloStep = ctrlInfo^0 -sbit ctrlShowFreq = ctrlInfo^1In service mode the weight can now manually be controlled. When infrared [kg] is pressed, the weight will show left/right/both.Then “0” is pressed before “print” in service mode, no printout! GUID from test map has been added to key_data.  Only Sweden Evaluation of axle removed from Swedish printout.If Pm is larger than +/- 0.2 bar during rolling resistance measuring, the Pm display will show lines “—“. If no P0 measured the Pm display will switch between lines “—“ and the block pressure after the test.When infrared [Ovality] is pressed, the tester will freeze values when average values are measured. (Same as eprom Version 12 ASB).

X010T_CHANGES: When config 29 = 1, the pedal force is added to brake force, the analog signal is then scaled 0-255 daN instead of 0-99 daN which is normal. The SR number is added to config 192 and is being sent with the key pack to the PC.Many customers have complained that the update rate of the display pointers was very slow. It is because the communication line is very busy. Many customers do not have an ECPU, so on power up the system will check if the ECPU is connected. If not, the communication to the ECPU will stop. A power cycle needs to be done to restart the communication.The time before middle roller speed check was hardcoded to 500mS. Config 107 is now added and makes it possible to adjust the time (Min 500mS and Max. 1500mS). The reason for this config is, that some testers with soft starters could not startup (Iceland).  If the car was thrown out of the rollers just after start it took 1sec before the motor was stopped. It is now fixed and the motor is stopped immediately.The sideslip value now has a max and a min value. +/-15. Ex. If sideslip measured is -26 it will be set to -15.The RS232 receive function is improved.   Iceland language is added.

X200T_CHANGES: NxPeak filter is now added to the live calculation of imbalance.Address 177 is added [Max CLS Load] 0: Not active1 – 15: Active (example 6=6000kg).The default values of following addresses have changed:Address 202 = 30 to 25Address 216 = 30 to 40Address 219 = 50 to 75Code optimization for saving space!Retest function added. After testing an axle, press F1+0 and use the arrow up/down to select the correct axle. New special printout is made for NZ. For NZ the total deceleration for both service and parking will be shown after the test. The eprom will send Ack on reset received from the PC by RS232    Slip warning fixed.Address 78 [Load regulating during brake test]The Address has changed. 0: No (Default) 	- “before Yes”	1: Yes 		- “before No”

X010T_CHANGES: Address 9 is added (B-Mode):0= B-Mode not active.1= B-Mode activeB-Mode is using right motorbrake output. So from now on motorbrake is only controlled with one output.Address 69 is added (Ovality in %)0= Ovality in brakeforce (daN)1= Ovality in %2= Ovality in +/- % (Ovality divided by 2)Problem with using IR remote and cable remote at the same time is fixed.If 2 single axles is testet, the eprom knows that it is a motorcycle. Testside in the keypack will now tell is left or right side is testet. (For Lituania "Jonas")

Starting the motors in SERVICE mode is not possible anymore.The brake force offset is now stored after about 20 sec with a quiet roller set (Same as X200). That is fixed. Only L2/L5:BM Standard language is added. BM Standard is a copy of NZ language, but without the special things for NZ.
